This Flex System Flex Slug/Security model shotgun goes from a slug gun to a home security gun and back again in minutes. The Flex System is based on the legendary model 500 and features a modular system of shotguns with TLS (Tool-Less Locking System) which consists of three connecting technologies (for the stock, forend and recoil pad) for a flexibility that allows easy changes for a specific needs. The Slug portion of the combo includes a 24-inch, vent-rib, ported fully-rifled barrel with an integral cantilevered scope base. It has a 4-position dual comb buttstock and forend finished with Mossy Oak Break-Up Infinity. The Security configuration features a black pistol grip and tri-rail tactical forend (with touchpad accommodation), with an 18.5-inch barrel with a cylinder bore and bead sight. The receiver and both barrels have a matte blue gunmetal finish.

We will ship weapons to any FFL in the continental United States for a flat rate fee of $20 for handguns and $30 for long guns. We will not ship firearms to individuals. A valid, signed copy of an FFL must be presented before firearms are released for shipment.  Precision Firearms only ships ammunition via UPS with varying fees depending upon the weight, call or email for pricing. All other products will ship via United States Postal Service unless otherwise requested with fees varying from $5.70 - $11.70 depending on size and weight of product.
Return Policy

Incorrect items: If a product is not the product that you ordered, Precision Firearms will either replace the product or give you a full refund if returned within 10 days of receipt. Precision Firearms cannot replace products that have been used, unless they are covered under the manufacturer's warranty, you will send these items directly to the manufacturer for replacement. Note: We do not accept returns on ammunition, scopes, binoculars, flashlights, software, DVD’s or hearing protectors. Special Order Items may not be returned.

Firearms are non-returnable and non-refundable. However, to insure your satisfaction with your new firearm, we do offer help in getting the firearm covered under the manufacturer’s warranty, terms and conditions of each individual manufacturer apply. Precision Firearms is not responsible for warranting firearms.

Manufacturer Warranty & Service: In some cases, it may be best to send your firearm directly to the manufacturer for repair or adjustment. Some manufacturers offer superior service and we may direct you in this regard, depending on the brand.
Used Gun Purchase (Buy Back): At our discretion, we may offer to buy a firearm, at a price to be determined by Precision Firearms.
Electronic Devices, Hearing Protectors, Lasers, Rangefinders, Lights and other electronic devices are covered by the manufacturer, and must be returned to the manufacturer for repair or replacement.
No refunds or returns are accepted on these types of items. We only carry Electronic Devices that are covered under warranty by a reputable manufacturer.
Please consult your owner’s manual for warranty information, or call us for instructions.

If you are not satisfied with your Accessory Product (other than exceptions such as firearms, electronic devices, optics etc.), you may return it within 10 days for a full refund, less shipping costs (and fees) and restocking fees (20% minimum restocking fee*). Item must be unused and in 100% original condition with all labels and papers intact. You must have a 'Return Authorization Number' (RMA) before returning the item. Contact us by phone or email for an RMA- BEFORE YOU RETURN THE PRODUCT! Accessories include (but are not limited to): Holsters, Belts, Knives, Cleaning Supplies, and Firearm Add-Ons. *Restocking fees: All returns will be charge a twenty percent restocking fee. Left Handed Items are special order items, and are not returnable. Left Handed Orders May Not Be Cancelled."

This is a very scarce pre-war Winchester Model 62A that is chambered for .22 Short only. The great majority of the Model 62 rifles were chambered for .22 Short, Long and Long Rifle A small fraction of the .22 Short only rifles were made for field use. These field guns are easily identified by the small rounded loading port (the gallery guns had a ""triangular"" loading port to be used with a speed loading device). Other than a handful of special order or experimental guns, the .22 Short Only Field rifles are the scarcest of all Model 62A's This rifle is in excellent, completely original condition. All components are original and correct including the pre-war high comb buttstock, large 17-groove pump handle, special short only carrier, etc. The original blue finish rates 99% with just enough aging to assure that it is 100% original. There is no significant rust or pitting. The stocks are in excellent condition, never sanded or refinished, and are free if cracks, chips, gouges, or repairs. The rifle is in excellent mechanical condition and has a mirror bright bore. According to serial number information, this fantastic little rifle was manufactured in the summer of 1941, just months before the USA entered the Second World War. A great gun, don't let this rare little Winchester get away"

It is a scale replica of a 17th-century Dutch East India Company ship.
Please note this is not one of the cheap, mass-produced toys made in a sweatshop in the Philippines that you commonly see sold in home-decor stores or online.

I've been building models for over 30 years. This model took me approximately one painstaking year to build. It is plank-on-frame construction; meaning that the hull, decks, and bulkheads were formed by laying down a miniature keel, building a frame skeleton, and applying separate planks one at a time via steam and pressure - just like the real thing (unlike the cheap models, which simply use a solid piece of wood.) The masts, shrouds, ratlines, rigging, tackle and blocks are all to scale and accurately portrayed (again, unlike models who's rigging is woefully thick, and not to scale.)
This is a LARGE model, measuring a little over 25 inches tall (from shelf to the top of the main mast), 26 inches long, and 8 inches wide (from tips of the main yardarm)
Unfortunately we've fallen on hard times and now I'm scrambling to make some extra cash.

This would serve as stunning showpiece for a fireplace mantle. Armslist only allows 3 images so please feel free to email me with questions or request additional images (there's plenty more). Pick-up only, as it's far to fragile to ship."

""The P-3AT is a semi-automatic, locked breech pistol, chambered for the .380 Auto cartridge. It has been developed from our highly successful P-32 pistol with negligible increase in weight and size.
The slidestop has been eliminated and the magazine capacity reduced to 6 rounds due to the larger cartridge. The firing mechanism is double action only. The magazine has a 6 round capacity.
The KEL-TEC P-3AT is the lightest .380 Auto pistol ever made. Thanks to its locking dynamics and superior ergonometry, perceived recoil and practical accuracy are comparable to much larger guns.

The P-3AT is mainly intended for plainclothes police officers as a secondary weapon, or for concealed carry by licensed citizens. The small grip size and light trigger pull make the P-3AT ideal for female shooters.

The P-3AT has five main component groups: barrel, slide, firing mechanism, grip, and magazine. The barrel is made of SAE 4140 ordnance steel, heat treated to 48 HRC. The slide is also 4140 steel, and contains the firing pin and the extractor.

The rectangular frame is machined from solid 7075-T6 aluminum and houses the firing mechanism. The trigger connects via a transfer bar to the hammer. The hammer is driven by a novel free floating extension spring. The light weight firing pin transmits the energy of the hammer to ignite the primer. After firing, the hammer block holds the hammer away from the firing pin, providing a mechanical safety.""
